text:
Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: W

Definition: Shorthand for win
Example: Got the job today, big W!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: L

Definition: Shorthand for loss/losing
Example: I forgot my wallet at home, that’s an L.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: L+ratio

Definition: Response to a comment or action on the internet that is particularly bad.
Example: Your tweet got 5 likes and 100 replies calling you out. L + ratio.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Dank

Definition: excellent or of very high quality
Example: That meme is so dank!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Cheugy

Definition: Derogatory term for Millennials. Used when millennials are perceived to be excessively attempting to be trendy or stylish.
Example: That phrase is so cheugy, no one says that anymore.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: TFW

Definition: That feeling when
Example: TFW you finish a big project and can finally relax

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Woke

Definition: being politically aware
Example: He’s really woke about climate change.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Bop

Definition: An excellent song or album.
Example: This new track is a total bop!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: G.O.A.T

Definition: The greatest of all time
Example: Michael Jordan is the GOAT of basketball.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Smol

Definition: Something that is small, and in most cases exceptionally adorable.
Example: Look at that smol puppy, it’s adorable!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Fam

Definition: Fam is a shorter word for family, but don't be fooled– it can be used to describe your friends or the way Millennials use "bro".
Example: What’s good, fam? Long time no see!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Glow up

Definition: a makeover or transformation from bad to good.
Example: She really had a glow up since high school.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Stan

Definition: Supporting something. Specifically used in some cases to the idolatry support of personalities.
Example: I stan BTS so hard!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Ghosting

Definition: common amongst the earlier talking stages of a relationship. Ghosting someone means you start ignoring them or stop texting them back.
Example: We were talking for weeks, and then she just ghosted me.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Salty

Definition: Used when someone feels jealous
Example: He’s just salty because he lost the game

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Sip tea

Definition: Gossiping (spilling the tea)
Example: I’m just here to sip tea and watch the drama unfold.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Drip

Definition: Another way of saying swag, drip is a term for a cool or sexy trend or style.
Example: His drip today is on point.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Iykyk

Definition: Acronym for "If you know, you know." Used to describe inside jokes.
Example: That hidden message in the movie was iconic. IYKYK.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Rent free

Definition: To be constantly thinking or upset about something.
Example: That song is living rent-free in my head

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Catch these hands

Definition: Used to threaten physical combat with someone
Example: If you keep talking like that, you’re gonna catch these hands.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Drag

Definition: If you drag someone, you're criticizing or making fun of them
Example: She dragged him for his terrible performance.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Bussin’

Definition: Used to say something is good. Primarily used to describe food
Example: This pizza is bussin’!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Snatched

Definition: If someone is looking snatched, they look really good, particularly their outfit
Example: Her makeup was snatched at the event.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Cancel culture

Definition: a form of shaming the actions or opinions of a public figure, company, or organization
Example: People are saying he’s canceled after those comments.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Ffs

Definition: For fuck sake
Example: FFS, why is this meeting taking so long?

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: e-boy

Definition: similar to emo or goth culture, but they use the internet to express themselves.
Example: He’s such an e-boy with those black nails and chains.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: e-girl

Definition: similar to emo or goth culture, but they use the internet to express themselves.
Example: She’s such an e-girl with her neon eyeliner and platform boots.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Big yikes

Definition: Used to describe something embarrassing.
Example: She wore the same dress as the bride at the wedding? Big yikes.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Finna

Definition: shortened term for saying "I'm going to"
Example: I’m finna head out.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: cap

Definition: A lie or exaggeration
Example: He said he’s a millionaire, but that’s cap.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: High-key

Definition: the opposite of being low-key.
Example: I high-key love this song.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Simp

Definition: Sycophancy, being overly affectionate in pursuit of a sexual relationship
Example: He buys her gifts every day, he’s such a simp.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Camp

Definition: Something that is ironically trendy. One might consider Crocs to be of the camp aesthetic.
Example: That outfit is so camp, it’s amazing.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Snack

Definition: a person that you find attractive
Example: He showed up to the party looking like a whole snack.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Take several seats

Definition: If someone is really getting on your nerves, you might tell them to take several seats.
Example: You’re being way too extra right now, take several seats.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Sheesh

Definition: To praise someone when they are doing something good. The one being praised is to do the "ice in my veins" pose popularized by Basketball player D'Angelo Russell.
Example: Sheesh, that’s a lot of money!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Hits different

Definition: Something that is better in a peculiar manner
Example: This song hits different at night.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Bet

Definition: Yes, ok, "it's on."
Example: You want to meet at 6? Bet.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Periodt

Definition: Used to add emphasis to something
Example: That’s the best movie of all time, periodt.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Finesse

Definition: Finesse means to trick or manipulate someone or a situation in order to get what you want.
Example: He finessed his way into the VIP section.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: I’m weak

Definition: Similar to "I'm dead", this is just another term to use when you find something hilarious
Example: That joke had me weak!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Main character

Definition: a phrase used to describe someone who is generally well-liked and charismatic. It can also be used to describe someone when they're making a scene, but not necessarily in a bad way
Example: She’s living her life like she’s the main character in a movie.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Sis

Definition: A shortened version of "sister", this term is typically used to greet a friend, no matter their gender.
Example: Sis, you are killing it in that outfit!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Sending me

Definition: Another term to use if you find something particularly funny.
Example: That meme is sending me!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Gaup

Definition: Money, and lots of it.
Example: I’m trying to stack up this gaup before the weekend.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: This ain’t it, chief

Definition: Another way of giving disapproval for something.
Example: That outfit? This ain’t it, chief.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Extra

Definition: Someone who is out there and enjoys taking things to a new level of flamboyance.
Example: She brought a whole suitcase for a weekend trip, she’s so extra.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Clapback

Definition: Swift and witty response to an insult or critique
Example: Her clapback to that troll was savage.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: @ me

Definition: Pronounced "at me." Used on social media when someone feels attacked by a post.
Example: I’m about to pull up, C me at the club!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Asl

Definition: Has two definitions. It can be used as a shortened version of "as hell." It can also be used as an acronym for age/sex/location.
Example: It’s cold asl outside!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Bang 30s

Definition: To get in a physical altercation with someone.
Example: He was out there bangin’ 30s all night.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Based

Definition: Originally meaning "to be your self and not care about how others view you", The word is now used to indicate an opinion or something that someone agrees with. It is especially common in political slang and discussions.
Example: He doesn’t care what anyone thinks, he’s so based.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Beat your face

Definition: To apply makeup to the face.
Example: I’m about to beat my face for this event tonight.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Big mad

Definition: Term used to describe when someone is excessively angry.
Example: He’s big mad because we beat his team last night.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Body count

Definition: A euphemism for how many people one has had sex with. Initially referred to specifically sexual intercourse, but was expanded to include all forms of sex.
Example: What’s your body count?

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Boujee

Definition: A high-class/materialistic person.
Example: We’re going to a boujee restaurant tonight.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Bussy

Definition: "Boy Pussy," i.e. a man's anus.
Example: He was joking about his bussy all night.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Cringe

Definition: A response to embarrassment or social awkwardness
Example: That performance was so cringe.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Ded

Definition: Used to describe something humorous to such an extent as to "kill you."
Example: That joke had me ded.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Facts

Definition: The truth
Example: Pizza is the best food ever. Facts.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Glow-up

Definition: A major improvement in one's self, usually an improvement in appearance, confidence, and style. Frequently used in a context relating to puberty.
Example: She had a major glow-up over the summer.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: I oop

Definition: Used to express shock, embarrassment, and or amusement.
Example: She spilled her drink on her dress and I oop!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: t's giving…

Definition: Describes the vibes or connotation of something.
Example: It’s giving 90s nostalgia with that outfit.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Lit

Definition: Colloquially: "Enlightened", "Hot", "Fire." The new hotness; something remarkable, interesting, fun or amusing. Generally positive.
Example: That party was lit!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Mid

Definition: Short for mediocre
Example: That movie was mid, nothing special.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Not you

Definition: Used to condemn or poke fun at someone or something.
Example: Not you eating the last slice of pizza!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: NPC

Definition: Someone who cannot think for themselves and/or has no or little control over their own life. Someone that is ready to agree with popular opinion unquestioningly and always believes what they are told. Gullible
Example: She’s acting like such an NPC, just going with the flow.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: OK boomer

Definition: Derogatory term directed towards Baby Boomers. Used as a response when boomers are deemed to be out of touch with younger generations
Example: You don’t understand memes? OK boomer.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: On god

Definition: Short for "I swear to god." Means that a person's statement is frank.
Example: I’m telling you, that was the best movie I’ve ever seen, on god!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Ratio

Definition: When an internet post has a comparable number of comments/replies to "likes", which is usually indicative of a poor reception.
Example: That tweet got ratio’d so bad, more people replied than liked it.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Rizz

Definition: One's courtship/seduction skills
Example: He’s got so much rizz, everyone likes him.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Sksksk

Definition: Used to convey happiness/laughter
Example: I spilled my drink sksksk.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Slaps

Definition: Used to refer to something (typically music) that is perceived to be good.
Example: This new track slaps!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Sus

Definition: Short for suspect/suspicious.
Example: Why’s he acting so sus all of a sudden?

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Slay

Definition: To do something well.
Example: She’s slaying in that outfit tonight!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Tea

Definition: Gossiping (spilling the tea)
Example: Spill the tea, I need to know what happened!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Understood the assignment

Definition: To understand what was supposed to be done; to do something well
Example: That outfit is fire, she really understood the assignment.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Valid

Definition: Understandable
Example: Those sneakers are valid!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Vibe Check

Definition: To check one's personality or attitude
Example: Vibe check: Are you good?

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Vibing

Definition: describes a generic positive feeling that someone has about something
Example: We were just vibing to some music all night.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Wig

Definition: To do something so well as to "make one's wig fly off."
Example: That performance was amazing, wig!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Word

Definition: Slang for "okay."
Example: Let’s meet at 7. Word

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Af

Definition: As fuck
Example: I’m tired af after that workout.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Big brain

Definition: When you have done something silly making you feel like your own brain shrinks as you regret all of your life
Example: He solved that puzzle in seconds, big brain moves.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Chad

Definition: Used to describe your typical alpha male
Example: He’s such a Chad, always winning at everything.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Clapped

Definition: To be completely and utterly destroyed.
Example: That car is clapped, it’s falling apart.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Clown

Definition: People who are completely unintelligent.
Example: I waited all day for him to text me back. I’m such a clown.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Cringy

Definition: anything that’s embarrassing or try-hard
Example: That old tweet was so cringy, I can’t believe I posted that.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: fomo

Definition: Fear of missing out
Example: I have major FOMO after seeing everyone’s vacation pics.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Fr

Definition: For real
Example: You’re moving to LA? Fr?

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: I can’t even

Definition: an expression commonly used when someone is feeling either so overjoyed or exasperated that they can’t even find the right words; depending on the context.
Example: Ion even care what they think.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Ion

Definition: I don’t
Example: This meme is too much, I can’t even!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: IRL

Definition: In Real Life
Example: Let’s meet IRL next week.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Karen

Definition: A stereotype for women who behave extremely unreasonably and childish – especially towards service staff or people of colour – and tend to invoke their racial privilege
Example: That woman asked to speak to the manager, total Karen move.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Low key

Definition: Secretly
Example: I’m low key excited about the new movie.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Mom

Definition: It just means to admire or look up to someone so much that you jokingly want to be adopted by them or have them as your second parent
Example: Beyoncé is such a mom.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Dad

Definition: It just means to admire or look up to someone so much that you jokingly want to be adopted by them or have them as your second parent
Example: Keanu Reeves is my dad.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: NGL

Definition: Not Gonna Lie
Example: NGL, that was a tough workout.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Pick me girl

Definition: Pick me girls are the type of girls who claim that they are nothing like other girls, in order to get attention from guys (also see ‘simping’ below). It’s a derogatory term.
Example: She’s such a pick me girl, always saying she’s not like other girls.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Boomer

Definition: Short for ‘baby boomer’, referring to older folks born 1946 to 1964 – but mostly used to clap back at pretty much anyone who’s older and not so in-the-know.
Example: My boss is such a boomer, doesn’t even know how to use Zoom.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Sleeping on

Definition: When you "sleep on" something, you overlook or underestimate it
Example: You’re sleeping on this new album, it’s so good.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Shade

Definition: Diss. Also: throwing shade; being shady.
Example: She was throwing shade at my outfit.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Shook

Definition: Surprised or shocked.
Example: I was shook when I found out the news.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Smh

Definition: Shake my head’. Another one for texting, smh usually signifies exasperation
Example: You forgot your homework again? Smh.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: TBH

Definition: short for “to be honest” and is usually used when making a comment or a joke (best to stick to texts with this one too).
Example: TBH, I didn’t enjoy the party last night.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Thirsty

Definition: Stands for desperate, usually for attention
Example: He’s been texting me nonstop, he’s so thirsty.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Thirst trap

Definition: a social media post intended to, uh, entice viewers and get attention.
Example: She posted a total thirst trap on Instagram.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Yas

Definition: A very enthusiastic and celebratory way of saying yes!
Example: Yas queen! You’re slaying that outfit!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Yeet

Definition: The Gen Z version of YOLO (you only live once). Usually exclaimed (pretty loudly) when doing something risky or throwing an item very hard (most of the time for absolutely no reason at all and with absolutely no aim).
Example: He yeeted the ball across the yard.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: ick

Definition: used to express disgust at something unpleasant or offensive.
Example: He talks with his mouth full, that gave me the ick.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: naur

Definition: means no or know. It functions as a more dramatic way of saying "no" or "know," and sounds like "no" with an Australian accent.
Example: Naur, why did you do that?

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Say less

Definition: A shortened version of "say no more."
Example: Want to grab dinner? Say less, I’m there.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Unserious

Definition: a more fun way of saying something or someone is ridiculous, or that it can't be taken seriously.
Example: You’re being so unserious about this important issue.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Gagged

Definition: To be “gagged” is to be shocked, amazed, et cetera.
Example: I was gagged when I saw her outfit!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Ate

Definition: If you “ate” something, it means you executed it extremely well.
Example: She ate that performance, no crumbs left.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Poggers

Definition: an expression that conveys excitement
Example: You won the game? Poggers!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Heather

Definition: any lovely person who seems like they’re the main character, evoking as much admiration as jealousy
Example: She’s such a Heather, everyone loves her.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Wth

Definition: What the hell
Example: You like pizza? I’m with it.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Flex

Definition: Used to describe someone showing off, gloating, or parading around.
Example: He’s flexing his new car all over social media.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Gucci

Definition: term born out of the popularity of the high-end fashion brand. These days, it means that something is good
Example: Everything is Gucci, don’t worry.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Hot girl summer

Definition: Hands down one of the biggest slang terms to hit pop culture in the summer of 2019, hot girl summer is about women having a good time and being unapologetic about who they are
Example: I’m ready for hot girl summer this year!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Sturdy

Definition: used to describe someone's dance moves. It's usually used in the phrase "get sturdy", which means that someone is performing a specific type of dance in which they move their legs, spin, and hop.
Example: He’s so sturdy on the dance floor!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Skill issue

Definition: used to blame someone for their own loss.
Example: You can’t beat the level? Sounds like a skill issue.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: TNTL

Definition: Trying not to laugh
Example: That meme is TNTL-worthy!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: G2G

Definition: Got to go
Example: Sorry, G2G! Talk later!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: YNK

Definition: You never know
Example: I might move abroad one day, YNK.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: CSL

Definition: Can’t stop laughing
Example: That joke was hilarious, CSL!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: GMTA

Definition: Great minds think alike
Example: You bought the same shoes as me? GMTA!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: IMO

Definition: In my opinion
Example: IMO, that movie wasn’t that great.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: IMOH

Definition: In my humble opinion
Example: IMOH, this is the best pizza place in town.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: JK

Definition: Just kidding
Example: You’re fired! JK, I could never fire you.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Bae

Definition: Short for “baby." Often a pet name for a crush or significant other.
Example: I’m spending the weekend with my bae.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: SSDD

Definition: Some stuff, different day
Example: How’s it going? SSDD.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: WYWH

Definition: Wish you were here
Example: The beach is amazing, WYWH!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Benching

Definition: Just like in sports, benching someone in dating means putting them to the side to date other people.
Example: I think he’s benching me—he texts but never makes plans.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Breadcumbing

Definition: When someone leads you on by flirting and making you feel special but without any intention to actually commit to a relationship.
Example: She’s breadcrumbing him, always texting but never wanting to meet.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Cuffing

Definition: "Cuffing" simply means to get into a relationship.
Example: Everyone’s cuffing this fall, it’s relationship season.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: DTR

Definition: Define the relationship
Example: We need to DTR soon, I need to know where we stand.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Gaslighting

Definition: refers to a form of psychological manipulation in which a significant other makes you feel crazy or wrong, even when unjustified
Example: He keeps telling me I’m overreacting, but I think he’s gaslighting me.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: ILY

Definition: I love you
Example: Goodnight, ILY!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Pink flags

Definition: Based on the idea of red flags, pink flags are on step down. They aren’t huge warning signals that something is wrong, but they can hint that this relationship isn’t super healthy
Example: She’s always late—kind of a pink flag, but not a dealbreaker.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Smash

Definition: means to have casual sex
Example: They hooked up last night, definitely a smash.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Situationship

Definition: Describes two people who are not officially dating but who have feelings for each other
Example: We’ve been hanging out a lot, but it’s just a situationship.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Zaddy

Definition: Refers to an attractive, well-dressed man. Often, it’s an older man
Example: Look at him in that suit, total zaddy vibes.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: Zombie-ing

Definition: This happens after someone ghosts you, and then decides to start talking to you again like nothing ever happened.
Example: He ghosted me months ago, and now he’s zombie-ing by texting me again.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: AFK

Definition: Away From Keyboard
Example: I’ll be AFK for 10 minutes, need to take a break.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: ASAP

Definition: As Soon As Possible
Example: I need that report ASAP!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: ATK

Definition: At The Keyboard
Example: I’m ATK, ready for the meeting.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: ATM

Definition: At The Moment
Example: I’m busy atm, can we talk later?

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: A3

Definition: Anytime, Anywhere, Anyplace
Example: Let’s meet up, I’m A3.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: BAK

Definition: Back At Keyboard
Example: I’m BAK, what did I miss?

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: BBL

Definition: Be Back Later
Example: I’m stepping out, BBL.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: BBS

Definition: Be Back Soon
Example: Grabbing a snack, BBS.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: BFN

Definition: Bye For Now
Example: Got to run, BFN!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: B4N

Definition: Bye For Now
Example: That troll got a BAN from the server.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: BRB

Definition: Be Right Back
Example: Need to grab my phone, BRB.”

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: BRT

Definition: Be Right There
Example: Just parking, BRT!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: BTW

Definition: By The Way
Example: BTW, I’ll be late to the party.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: B4

Definition: Before
Example: I need to finish this B4 I go out.

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: B4N

Definition: Bye For Now
Example: Heading out, B4N!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: CU

Definition: See You
Example: It was fun hanging out, CU later!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: CUL8R

Definition: See You Later
Example: Got to go, CUL8R!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: CYA

Definition: See You
Example: CYA tomorrow!

Task: Explain the internet slang.
Term: FAQ

Definition: Frequently Asked Questions
Example: Check the FAQ before you ask questions.
